<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0511d97b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s129"><num value="129">§ 129.</num><heading> Discriminating duties</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No part of the additional or discriminating duty imposed by law on merchandise on account of its importation in foreign vessels shall be allowed to be drawback, but the whole shall be retained.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0511d97c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(R.S. § 3027.)</sourceCredit>
